# Managed unit inventory consumed by scripts/deploy.sh.
#
# deploy.sh watches these units for an active-state regression across a deploy:
# a unit that was active BEFORE and is not active AFTER fails the deploy and
# triggers rollback. The effective UNIT_SET is the union of:
#   (a) the names listed here, and
#   (b) the basenames of every deploy/*.service shipped on origin/main
#       (excluding *.example.service).
# Repo-shipped units come from (b) automatically, so a PR that renames one of
# them shows up in this diff. List here ONLY the external/system units the bot
# depends on that are NOT shipped as deploy/*.service.
#
# One unit name per line; '#' starts a comment. deploy.sh hard-fails at start if
# this file is missing (it never substitutes a silent default).
#
# IMPORTANT: verify every name against the actual host
# (`systemctl list-unit-files`). A wrong name is skipped (and printed), never a
# hard fail — so a typo here silently drops a unit from the safety net.

# --- External backend services (not shipped as deploy/*.service) ---
xray.service
awg-quick@awg0.service
awg-quick@out-warp.service
danted.service
mtproxy.service                 # repo ships only a drop-in (deploy/mtproxy-vpn-bot-managed.conf)

# --- Names to confirm on the host (PR #222 renamed some vpnbot-* -> vpn-bot-,
#     but not the Hysteria2/WARP units) ---
vpnbot-hy2-warp-mark.service    # VERIFY exact unit name on host
